          "E4": {
            "channelId": "1420112347749416981",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "📍 E4 | Professor Oak's Lab",
              "description": "> Professor Oak’s lab rises like a beacon of curiosity at the edge of Pallet Town, its whitewashed walls lined with shelves groaning under stacks of well-worn journals, faded maps, and the occasional Poké Ball gleaming under the light.\n\nInside, rows of softly humming computers mingle with earthy scents drifting from planters of rare herbs and grasses, giving the space a feeling of both cutting-edge science and living nature. Wide windows flood the room with sunlight, illuminating charts of evolutionary trees pinned to corkboards and half-scribbled notes tacked beside them, capturing the restless mind of a man who has spent his life bridging discovery with care.\n\nAt the heart of the lab lies Oak’s research floor, where tables are crowded with microscopes, specimen jars, and gadgets designed to measure everything from wing beats to static discharge.",
              "image": "https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1420100291251933224/1420101702320918541/Professor_Oaks_Laboratory.webp?ex=68d42c46&is=68d2dac6&hm=46403b6d596c652148ba015d6f9691d4cbe5cc44d51ccac8d334ce36017fac77&=&format=webp&width=1080&height=607",
              "clues": []
            },
