              "title": "🌿 Beneath the Boulder",
              "content": "You crouch beside the boulder, brushing aside a curtain of reeds. The grass around it is unnaturally pressed flat—less like wind, more like someone—or something—rested here. As your fingers graze the edge of the stone, something metallic catches the light.\n\nYou pry up a patch of moss, revealing a narrow crevice beneath the boulder. Tucked just out of sight is a small, tarnished pouch. Its drawstring is frayed, but the weight inside is unmistakable. You’ve found a stash of gold—forgotten, or deliberately hidden.",
