      "repair_sword_600g_973056": {
        "id": "repair_sword_600g_973056",
        "name": "Repair Sword (600g)",
        "label": "Repair Sword (600g)",
        "emoji": null,
        "style": 3,
        "actions": [
          {
            "type": "display_text",
            "order": 0,
            "config": {
              "title": "🗡️ The Old Man’s Forge – Sword Repair",
              "content": "*You place a splintered, ancient sword on the old man’s anvil, along with a pouch of coins.*\n\n**You:** “Can this be repaired?”\n\n**Old Man** *(narrowing his eyes, running a hand over the warped edge)*:  \n“Well now… this isn’t just iron and luck. You feel that?”  \n*He closes his palm around the hilt. The sword hums faintly in response.*  \n“Still alive, this one. Barely—but the spine’s intact. Just needs to remember what it was.”\n\n> *He pulls open a drawer beneath the bench and produces a long, thin shard—coiled like bone, and glowing with a pale light. It flares faintly as it nears the broken blade.*\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“Kept this sealed for decades. Came from a ruin that reeked of divine magic. Never knew what it wanted… until now.”\n\n> *The forge ignites. Silver sparks shower the stone. You hear ringing—high, harmonic—like a chorus of strings pulling taut. The reforging takes hours, but when it ends, the weapon gleams with buried memory.*\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“There. No mistaking what it is now. That sword’s older than any of us, and twice as stubborn. Be sure you’re its wielder—not its next victim.”\n\n**You:** “Thank you.”\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“Hah. I just shaped what was already there. It was waiting for someone. Looks like it chose.”\n\n```Note: The old man returns the remnants of your broken sword—they remain in your inventory, though their purpose is spent. The reforging has drawn out all that mattered. You now carry the restored weapon… and what’s left of the past.```",
              "image": "",
              "color": "#00ff00"
            },
            "executeOn": "true"
          },
          {
            "type": "give_item",
            "order": 1,
            "config": {
              "itemId": "_898695",
              "quantity": 1,
              "limit": {
                "type": "unlimited"
              }
            },
            "executeOn": "true"
          },
          {
            "type": "give_currency",
            "order": 2,
            "config": {
              "amount": -600,
              "limit": {
                "type": "unlimited"
              }
            },
            "executeOn": "true"
          },
          {
            "type": "display_text",
            "order": 3,
            "config": {
              "title": "🗡️ The Old Man’s Forge – Failed Sword Repair",
              "content": "> *You approach the anvil, something ancient stirring in your grip… but it’s not enough.*\n\n**Old Man** *(not looking up, but somehow knowing)*:  \n“Hm. That won’t do.”\n\n> *He extends a weathered hand, waiting… then slowly lowers it, empty.*\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“Tools like this don’t come to life on wishes alone. Steel’s only part of the price.”\n\n> *His gaze flicks briefly to the forge, where the embers sputter and dim, refusing to catch.*\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“The forge knows what’s missing. And it won’t move for less.”\n\n> *He turns his back, voice already trailing into the smoke.*\n\n**Old Man:**  \n“Return when you carry more than just hope. The blade remembers the difference.”",
              "image": "",
              "color": "#ff0000"
            },
            "executeOn": "false"
          }
        ],
        "trigger": {
          "type": "button",
          "button": {
            "label": "Repair Sword (600g)",
            "emoji": "🗡️",
            "style": "Primary"
          }
        },
        "conditions": [
          {
            "id": "cond_1755533979723_4gedi",
            "type": "currency",
            "operator": "gte",
            "value": 600,
            "logic": "AND"
