          "G4": {
            "channelId": "1431901364618788976",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🪓 G4 | Sreng Borderlands",
              "description": "> You stand on the windswept edge of Garreg Mach’s known world, where the plains begin to crack and rise into the wild reaches of the Sreng Borderlands. Coarse, golden grass whips at your boots, and the soil grows looser, dustier—stamped by the hooves of raiders long passed. The land here feels unsettled, not quite Fódlan and not quite foreign, but something in between.\n\nScrapwood totems and crude stone markers jut from the earth like bones, weathered by time and tension. A distant war horn—faint and uncertain—carries on the breeze. Was it just your imagination? Or is someone watching from the rise?\n\nThe path forks near a leaning post carved with faded Srengish runes. One route climbs toward the cliffs, the other snakes toward the open steppe.\nA bundle of feathers lies scattered in the grass… perhaps a warning. Or a remnant.\n\nSomeone has left a crude map etched into a stone slab. Its markings don’t match any Fódlan chart.",
              "image": null,
              "clues": []
            },
            "buttons": [
              "inspect_map_012154"
            ],
            "hiddenCommands": {},
