          "G5": {
            "channelId": "1431901400538943571",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "🪨 G5 | Fódlan's Throat",
              "description": "> A steep mountain range runs along the border between Fodlan and Almyra. That mountain range is called Fodlan's Throat. The sturdy fortress built within those mountains is called Fodlan's Locket. It occupies the only safe path through. \n\nUntil recently, Fodlan's Locket - and therefore, Fodlan's throat - was occupied by Almyrian forces. Now it is free for passage once again, but it is not without it's dangers still. \n\nA faint shimmer catches your eye near one of the large boulders of the landscape. At the base of a cliff, the grass seems slightly parted - flattened in a way that suggests more than just the wind.\n\nTall Reeds and Wildflowers sit on the edge of a small pond nearby, blowing softly in the wind. \n\nStanding near the entrance to Fodlan's Locket is Hubert.",
              "image": null,
              "clues": []
            },
            "buttons": [
              "cave_entrance_grass_802536",
