          "F6": {
            "channelId": "1431901455953956995",
            "baseContent": {
              "title": "⛵F6 | Arundel Shores",
              "description": "> Craggy promontories fall steeply into the sea here at Arundel Shores, where the roaring ocean meets the edge of the Adrestian coast. Once a minor docking point for supplies bound for the noble courts, the bay now lies half-forgotten—salt-worn moorings sag unused, and the remains of a weather-beaten watchtower cling to a rocky outcrop, scarred by storms and neglect.\n\nThe winds carry the pungent spray of the sea and the echo of distant gull calls. Driftwood heaps in crescent shapes against the shore, and a half-buried crest-bearing helm bears silent testament to a past skirmish or perhaps a failed sea rescue. Tide pools reflect mottled skies and tell of hidden life beneath the surface—bright barnacles, glinting shells, and a lone silver starfish nestled among stone.\n\nSomething in the water shifts.",
              "image": null,
              "clues": []
            },
            "buttons": [],
            "hiddenCommands": {},
